# Markdown Syntax Guide by Krishna

<!-- This file contains basic Markdown syntax for reference. -->

## 1. Headers
<!-- Use `#` for headers. The number of `#` symbols indicates the level. -->

# H1 Header
## H2 Header
### H3 Header
#### H4 Header

## 2. Emphasis
<!-- Use `**` for bold and `*` or `_` for italics. -->

**This text is bold**  
*This text is italic*  
_This text is also italic_

## 3. Lists
### Unordered Lists
<!-- Use `-`, `+`, or `*` to create unordered lists. -->

- Item 1
- Item 2
  - Subitem 2a
  - Subitem 2b

### Ordered Lists
<!-- Use numbers followed by a period for ordered lists. -->

1. First item
2. Second item
3. Third item

## 4. Links
<!-- Create hyperlinks using `[link text](URL)`. -->

[OpenAI](https://www.openai.com)

## 5. Images
<!-- Embed images using `![alt text](image URL)`. -->

![Markdown logo](https://example.com/logo.png)

## 6. Blockquotes
<!-- Create blockquotes using `>`. -->

> This is a blockquote.

## 7. Code
### Inline Code
<!-- Use backticks ` to mark inline code. -->

Here is some `inline code`.

### Code Blocks
<!-- Use triple backticks ``` or indentation to create code blocks. -->


## 8. Horizontal Rule
<!-- Create a horizontal rule using three hyphens `---` or asterisks `***`. -->

---

## 9. Tables
<!-- Create tables using pipes `|` and hyphens `-` for columns and rows. -->

| Header 1 | Header 2 |
|----------|----------|
| Row 1    | Data 1   |
| Row 2    | Data 2   |

## 10. Task Lists
<!-- Use `- [ ]` for unchecked tasks and `- [x]` for checked tasks. -->

- [ ] Task 1
- [x] Task 2 (completed)

## 11. Footnotes
<!-- Use `[^1]` to create a footnote reference and define it later in the document. -->

Here is a footnote reference[^1].

[^1]: This is the footnote text.

## 12. Newlines
<!-- To create a newline, end a line with two spaces or insert a `<br>` tag. -->

This is the first line.  
This is the second line.

<!-- Alternatively: -->

This is the first line.<br>This is the second line.

## 13. Special Characters
<!-- Escape special characters by preceding them with a backslash `\`. -->

\*This text is not italicized*  
\# This text is not a header  
\> This is not a blockquote  
\[Link Text](#) is displayed as plain text